item.title: Much of Florida under state of emergency as possible tropical storm forms in Gulf of Mexico
item.description: Forecasters are warning of possible flash flooding and landslides across the eastern Yucatan peninsula and western Cuba, and Florida is bracing for a possible hurricane by midweek, as a weather system off the coast of Mexico is expected to become a tropical storm by Sunday.
item.dc:creator: Terry Spencer, Associated Press, KPRC 2
